args:
Finni will be deactivated if she can't destroy
Laxi, so Eirene devises a plan to protect her
that involves invading the Halidom and making
off with Mascula's abandoned body.
All right, time to do this.\nI'm gonna crush everybody!
▷That's far enough! You'll cause no\nfurther destruction to this city!◁

If it ain't the unit packing a mana kiln.
Too bad, because while I want nothing
more than to repay you for before,
I was ordered not to fight you.
▷After her, Laxi! She could lose control\nof herself at any moment!◁
First, we must prioritize confirming\nthe location of the lead unit.
▷Hey, yeah. Where DID that\nEirene lady go?◁

We lack the data to determine that.
However...
▷You have a bad feeling about it?
Yeah, me too.◁
They've left some forces here, but the\nwatch seems lax—just as her memories\nindicated it would be.
According to Laxi's memory,\nit is just beyond here...
You there! Stop skulking around\nin the dark and face me!
Huh? Oh, hey, an android.\nYou a friend of Laxi or something?
(It will be best to play along...)
Yes. She asked me to come here and\nretrieve an item she had forgotten.
You hoofed it a hell of a long way\njust to pick up some gear.
Yes, and as I must hurry back, I fear I\ncannot stay for further pleasantries.\nI hope you will not think ill of me.
HA! You think I actually fell for that?!
If Laxi really did ask you to do something,\nyou wouldn't be sneaking in here like\nsome justice-lacking creeper!
Time to face the Karlsplosion, villain!
I suppose it was wishful thinking to\nthink you'd be fooled by that...
Obviously! My justice never yields to evil!
Seriously, Karl, enough with the yelling.\nWhat are you on about this time?!
(Tsk. This is getting out of hand.)
Your sense of justice is keenly honed if\nyou can tell all that from a glimpse!
I don't need a sense of ＂justice＂ to know\nsome stranger lurking in the shadows is\nup to no good, you dope!
No need for modesty! Shout your justice\nout to the very heavens themselves!
I'm afraid I don't have time to play\nwith you.
I'LL be the one to decide when and how\nthis little encounter ends, lady!
You're going to tell us why you snuck into\nthe Halidom, even if I have to get rough!
You can give up on that. Androids don't\nfeel pain, so you can't really threaten me.\nAnd I'm done here, so goodbye.
She was speaking as though she had\naccomplished her objective, but what in\nthe world was she...? Oh no. This is bad!
What's wrong?! Are you all right?!\nDo you need justice?!
What we need isn't justice!\nWhat we need is to contact\nPrince {player_name} right now!
The more I inquire, the more peculiar\nthese androids become.
There is no doubt they're based on us, yet\nthe technology gap has created some clear\nimperfections in their systems.

If that were all they were, they'd just be
poor imitations...but they also contain
some components that are proving
impossible to decipher.

...This isn't working. I won't be able to
get any further with the equipment here...
And I'm no closer to understanding how
their hearts were combined.
But even if I gave this to Anassa,\nshe wouldn't use the analyzed\ntechnology to help Finni.
?! Was that communication from Finni?\nSomething was clearly wrong...\nWhat's happening? Finni!
What's going on?! This level of damage\nshouldn't have occurred simply from\ntoday's operation!
I have a report for the unit Eirene.\nDuring today's operation, the unit Finni\nonce again fell into an uncontrolled state.
While in this state, unit Finni caused\nsubstantial damage to allied units.\nEx Machina can no longer overlook this.
The Humanoid Liberation Agency has\nruled that unit Finni is to be scrapped.
I request revocation of that ruling! Please!
The Agency's ruling is absolute.\nThere will be no revocation.
I won't let Finni be scrapped!
I have observed significant issues in unit\nEirene's conduct regarding this matter.
There is concern that the matter of\nscrapping unit Finni is having an impact\non unit Eirene's performance.
While the ruling cannot be repealed\nit is up to me to determine the method\nand timing for scrapping unit Finni.
Unit Finni will be given a single chance:
If unit Finni can destroy the mana-kiln-\nequipped android in the next operation,\nI will put off scrapping her indefinitely.
...! Understood...\nI will ensure that Finni destroys her target.
I swear I'll protect you, Finni...
(No matter what means I must turn to.)
